column49: I'm sure that for 99% of the teachers they are so thankful for the changes to the website and the easier way to place classroom orders. I'm a very small preschool in a very rural part of Indiana. My parents are low income/poverty level people. They want something better for their children and want to buy books but can't always afford to. I order for my students on most of my orders so everyone gets a book a few times a year. I'm concerned about parents knowing who paid for their child's book. I wish there were a way that parents could pay me and I would turn in the order so no one would know if a parent didn't pay me.

column49: One of the main incentive for me to order from Scholastic was the beginning of the year Bonus Points deal. I order throughout the year to use those bonus points. Moving from 5 bonus points for every dollar from orders over $300 get 10,000 bonus points is a huge disappointment. You are reducing my bonus points from 10,000 to 1,500. The selection of books has also been reduced drastically. I have been a golden apple teacher for years, but it is to the point now where Scholastic is not worth the amount of time it takes to send flyers and reminders, and collect money, and then sort and pass out books... I am not sure I will use Scholastic anymore.

column49: As I am searching through the site for the new year, I am continually disappointed with each page I browse.     For the last 10 years, I have fundraised so that I could purchase books for my student. I collect $10 per child and use those funds to purchase monthly books for my students. There used to be a $1 book each month. Then those were phased out, and the $1 book of the week was fine usually. It was also nice to have the 5-book packs and the 10-book packs for $5 and $10 respectively.  I typically spend enough at Scholastic that I was also able to shop the $1 book store after spending the required amount. Through all of these ways, I have been able to  provide my students with a brand new book each month.      This year, I will not be able to do it. I have raised $300, but there are no $1 or equivalent book offers. Prices on the books are the same as Amazon, if not higher. I will have to raise at least double what I raised to even get whatever $2 book, and it's just not worth it.

column49: I am really disappointed in the changes to the bonus points program. I save and fundraise every year so that I can make a $300+ purchase and earn 10,000 Bonus Points.
